            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19940",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with SVN-8852",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-16T04:52:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-16T04:52:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20140",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm assuming this fix is merged to the 1.5 release branch for release with 1.5.1. Please update JIRA if this is not the case.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-21T17:11:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-21T17:11:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20507",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\n\ni think this fix does not confirm to the data type of parameter $conditionalStylesheet, because it should be a string and not a boolean.\n\nSo, if the stylesheets to include come from an array like this:\n<?php\nif (is_array($this->layout()->metaHeader['css'])) {\n    foreach ($this->layout()->metaHeader['css'] as $key => $array) {\n        echo $this->headLink()->appendStylesheet($array['href'], $array['media'], $array['conditionalStylesheet']); \n    }\n}\n?>\n\nthen usually the value of $array['conditionalStylesheet'] is a string or an empty string, but not a boolean. And the code wouldn't work like before the fix.\n\nSo instead of \n\nif (false !== $conditionalStylesheet) {\n                $conditionalStylesheet = (string) $conditionalStylesheet;\n}\n\nwould be correct\n\nif (!empty($conditionalStylesheet)) {\n                $conditionalStylesheet = (string) $conditionalStylesheet;\n}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-27T16:44:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-27T16:44:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20509",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't know from where you have you information but conditionalStylesheet should be a boolean.\n\nThe problem is only if you process the data and your boolean is converted to an string. A boolean false is converted to an string \"false\" and this was not recognised. Therefore this patch has been added.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-27T17:04:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-27T17:04:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20510",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "A boolean value true doesn't make sense, because the output would be like this:\n<!--[if  1]> <link ...  \/><![endif]-->\n\n\nOnly a string does make sense here, like this\n\n\n$array['conditionalStylesheet'] = ' lte IE 7';\n\n\nThen the output would be like this\n\n<!--[if  lte IE 7]> <link ...  \/><![endif]-->\n\n\nA boolean false or true generates invalid output.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-27T19:05:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-27T19:05:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20511",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "please read the \"Syntax of Conditional Comments\":\n\nhttp:\/\/msdn2.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms537512.aspx\n\n\nThe last two items in the example are true and false. But true and false are only two options of a few more possible values like IE, !IE, IE 5,  lt IE 5.5, ...\n\nAnd true|false must be given as strings to the Zend method appendStylesheet(), otherwise the output is irregular and senseless like a posted above.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-27T19:24:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-27T19:24:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20513",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but I still do not see the problem...\n\nSee the code from the core:\n{code}\n        if (0 < count($args)) {\n            $conditionalStylesheet = array_shift($args);\n            if (false !== $conditionalStylesheet) {\n                $conditionalStylesheet = (string) $conditionalStylesheet;\n            }\n        }\n{code}\n\nAs you can see the stylesheet is used as is.\nONLY if the stylesheet is given as boolean, it will be converted to a string as defined also by msdn where you refered to. An empty string would be ignored by compact.\n\nAnd as you can see under the msdn link a <IF false> or <IF true> is also handled as expected.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-28T02:24:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-28T02:24:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20515",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "If $conditionalStylesheet is a boolean it won't be converted to strings \"false\" or \"true\" but to strings \"\" or \"1\". That's the bug.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-28T08:21:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-28T08:21:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20516",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Ans also the doci is incorrect, because $conditionalStylesheet must be a string not a boolean. But a string \"true\" or \"false\" make sense, that's thinking error in my opinion.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=david+toniolo",
                        "name": "david toniolo",
                        "displayName": "David Toniolo",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-28T08:24:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-28T08:24:46.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
